{"id":14881034,"mediaExerciseId":"bff7b031-489d-44b0-a12b-26591dc46811","exerciseName":"7","chapterName":"7","chapterTitle":"Interest Rates and Bond Valuation","groupId":null,"groupTitle":null,"isPremium":true,"sectionName":"7.7","sectionTitle":"Determinants of Bond Yields","pageNumber":230,"solutions":[{"id":5976598,"modifiedOn":"2021-01-01T00:00:00.000000","steps":[{"columns":[{"text":"This task asks **to determine the term structure and explain the yield curve and the components of the bond yield.**","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":68,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/01/88fd7e05bcc9b21d54ab8a4d1cd9cdb3/7b0215257def16b9c7c0d1243a0eab1c/lateximg_large.png","width":995},"regular":{"height":34,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/01/88fd7e05bcc9b21d54ab8a4d1cd9cdb3/7b0215257def16b9c7c0d1243a0eab1c/lateximg.png","width":498}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":1},{"columns":[{"text":"**a)**\n\nLet's start with an explanation of term structure. It tells us the pure discount bond of long and short-term interest rates. These rates do not include the risk of default and tell us the different money values for a different period. The term structure depends on the following three elements: **real rate, interest rate risk, and inflation.** ","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":218,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/01/88fd7e05bcc9b21d54ab8a4d1cd9cdb3/a044d4265b37841bf7c1f5c4b4017d2c/lateximg_large.png","width":997},"regular":{"height":110,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/01/88fd7e05bcc9b21d54ab8a4d1cd9cdb3/a044d4265b37841bf7c1f5c4b4017d2c/lateximg.png","width":499}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":2},{"columns":[{"text":"The biggest impact has future inflation. A prediction the future long-term interest rate higher than short-term will cause an upward-sloping term structure. In contrast, a long-term interest rate lower than a short-term interest rate will cause a downward-sloping term structure. ","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":141,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/01/88fd7e05bcc9b21d54ab8a4d1cd9cdb3/3763e65802ff204594fb7a1fd3beb1a8/lateximg_large.png","width":1041},"regular":{"height":72,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/01/88fd7e05bcc9b21d54ab8a4d1cd9cdb3/3763e65802ff204594fb7a1fd3beb1a8/lateximg.png","width":520}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":3},{"columns":[{"text":"Interest rate risk increase if the term of maturity is longer. That is the reason why the premium for interest rate risk increases. The premium for interest rate is what investors require while investing in the long term to protect themselves from interest rate risk. \n\nAnd the real rate has the lowest impact on the term structure. High real rates cause higher interest rates.","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":216,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/01/88fd7e05bcc9b21d54ab8a4d1cd9cdb3/398ac8cb455e967588fbdca735fdd1ab/lateximg_large.png","width":997},"regular":{"height":110,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/01/88fd7e05bcc9b21d54ab8a4d1cd9cdb3/398ac8cb455e967588fbdca735fdd1ab/lateximg.png","width":499}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":4},{"columns":[{"text":"**b)**\n\n**A Treasury yield** curve is the term structure but is based on the bond yields. It is a structure that tells us how the bond yields depend on maturity.","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":105,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/01/88fd7e05bcc9b21d54ab8a4d1cd9cdb3/9a7b3e3ba2367a1fba6b12bb6fc90032/lateximg_large.png","width":996},"regular":{"height":53,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/01/88fd7e05bcc9b21d54ab8a4d1cd9cdb3/9a7b3e3ba2367a1fba6b12bb6fc90032/lateximg.png","width":497}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":5},{"columns":[{"text":"**c)**\n\nThe following six components defined the bond yield:\n\n- the real rate of interest\n- default risk\n- taxability\n- an absence of liquidity\n- prediction for the future inflation\n- interest rate risk","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":143,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/01/88fd7e05bcc9b21d54ab8a4d1cd9cdb3/41fb6319b8455eee407a5e66487b1573/lateximg_large.png","width":997},"regular":{"height":72,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/01/88fd7e05bcc9b21d54ab8a4d1cd9cdb3/41fb6319b8455eee407a5e66487b1573/lateximg.png","width":498}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":6}],"rating":5,"solutionUuid":"342bc1c6-5d3a-4c50-8143-45f7c2fb01cb","editorVersion":2,"answeredOn":null,"ratingCount":null,"solutionOrder":null,"totalSteps":6}],"textbook":{"authors":"Bradford D. Jordan, Randolph W. Westerfield, Stephen A. Ross","imageUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/textbook_covers/tmpm0p82b7h","imageThumbnailUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/cache/d1/d3/d1d34d106dd29dd2e71be582412ef59d.jpg","id":34320,"isbn":"9781259918957","isPremium":true,"title":"Fundamentals of Corporate Finance","edition":"12th Edition","verifiedSolutionCount":1217,"shouldBeIndexableForSeo":true,"modified":1665448474394,"active":true,"publisher":"McGraw-Hill Education","mainTextbookIsbn":null,"subjects":{"level1":["Social Science"],"level2":["Economics"],"level3":["Finance"]}},"nextExercises":[{"id":14881035,"exerciseName":"1","page":232,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"872a2c5d-c379-4099-8cdf-6c39c0b419b4","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-7-exercises-1-872a2c5d-c379-4099-8cdf-6c39c0b419b4"},{"id":14881036,"exerciseName":"2","page":232,"hasSolution":t